{{Advert|date=August 2010}} {{Infobox book |name = A Return to Love |author = [[Marianne Williamson]] |image = File:Returntolove.jpg |caption = Paperback 1993 |genre = [[Self-help]] |language = English |publisher = [[HarperCollins]] |release_date = 1992 |pages = 336 | isbn = 0-06-092748-8 | dewey= 299/.93 20 | congress= BP605.C68 W56 1996 | oclc= 317503896 }} '''''A Return to Love: Reflections on the Principles of [[A Course in Miracles]]''''' (1992) is the first book by author [[Marianne Williamson]] and a [[The New York Times Best Sellers List|''New York Times'' Best seller]].
==Exposure== ''A Return to Love'' spent 39 weeks on the New York Times best sellers list in 1992.<ref>{{cite news |title=BEST SELLERS: November 29, 1992|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/11/29/books/best-sellers-november-29-1992.html |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=November 29, 1992|accessdate=December 30, 2013}}</ref> A decade later, ''A Return to Love'' was credited as being one of the two books that helped bring [[New Age]] perspectives to the American mainstream.<ref>[http://www.publishersweekly.com/article/CA319870.html?pubdate=9%2F1%2F2003&display=archive ''Publisher's Weekly'' September 1, 2003]</ref>
Twenty years after her first appearance with the book, Williamson was interviewed again by Oprah Winfrey in July 2012, this time in a ''[[Super Soul Sunday]]'' (OWN TV) episode titled, "20 Years After A Return to Love".<ref>{{cite web | title =Oprah and Marianne Williamson: 20 Years After A Return to Love |publisher=OWN TV, Super Soul Sunday | url = http://www.oprah.com/own-super-soul-sunday/Full-Episode-Oprah-and-Marianne-Williamson-Video |date=July 29, 2012|accessdate = 2013-12-30 }}</ref> [[Robert Todd Carroll]], of ''[[The Skeptic's Dictionary]]'', writes, "Williamson might be called Oprah's patron saint. She's all about love and healing, yin and yang, being wounded, and using love and prayer to heal all wounds. ''A Return to Love: Reflections on the Principles of A Course In Miracles'' (1992) was number one on the ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'' non-fiction best-sellers list for 11 weeks. Williamson promoted her book and ACIM when she appeared on the ''Oprah Winfrey Show'', an episode that received more pro viewer mail than any other show for 1992. She also spoke of the book, and the course when she was interviewed by [[Barbara Walters]] on the ABC television news show [[20/20 (US television series)|''20/20'']].<ref>[http://skepdic.com/cim.html#*** ''Skeptics Dictionary'' ACIM listing] Retrieved June 30, 2006</ref>
