'''Simon Combes''' (1940 – 12 December 2004) was an artist born in [[Shaftesbury]], [[England]].  Residing most of his life in [[Kenya]], Combes was well known for his paintings of African wildlife and dedication to conservation.<ref name="AFC">[http://www.natureartists.com/artists/artist_biography.asp?ArtistID=452 Artists For Conservation: Simon Combes Biography]</ref>

In February 2005, the Artists For Conservation organization created a conservation award in the artist's honor.<ref name="Simon Combes Award">[http://www.natureartists.com/news_events/press_releases.asp?NewsID=459 Artists For Conservation: Simon Combes Award]</ref>

